# e2e-engineering engineering flow

When the user wants the full engineering flow ("e2e-engineering", "e2e-eng", "ship-it", "ship it", "implement feature X", "write e2e for X", "build end to end", "run the full flow"), follow the flow defined in [AGENTS.md](mdc:AGENTS.md).

Summary of the contract (full detail in AGENTS.md and `.agents/skills/`):

- **Three phases:** Pre-implementation (idea → approved PRD) · Implementation (slices → green tests) · Post-implementation (review + human QA).
- **Five hard gates — never skip:** (1) PRD approved, (2) failing test before production code, (3) debug escalation after 3 strikes, (4) full E2E suite green, (5) verification-before-completion.
- **State** lives in `.e2e-engineering/`: `prd.json` (sole-writer), `progress.txt` (append-only per task), `test-cases/*.md`, `constitution.md`.
- **Slices** follow the `depends_on` DAG (tracer → schema → logic → api → ui). Parallelism depends on the runtime's subagent capability probes.
- **Per slice:** re-read constitution → gap-check → red → green → refactor → feature E2E. 3 failed fixes → one systematic-debugging pass → else mark `blocked`.
- **Constitution** (coding + testing standards) is under `skills/e2e-engineering/constitution.md`; re-read before each slice.

For Claude Code entry points, install with: `npx e2e-engineering init --target claude`.
